** Control Alt Deceit :: Now Available for Purchase **We had a blast playing / testing / working on Control Alt Deceit. All Indiegogo orders have been fulfilled and we're now looking ahead to distribution.We can't thank our backers enough for helping us create such a high-quality product. It looks amazing and it's a lot of fun to play. If you wish to purchase a copy for yourself or someone else (Xmas is coming!), you can do so right here.     // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // // //  How it WorksThe Year is 1983...Your friends made a terrible decision — They entered your market. Once every player is assigned an Unfair Advantage card, market domination can begin.A great business needs a Product, Clients and Marketing; yours is no different. Build your business' value, raise capital, pile up competitive advantages and keep some cash for defense...  Why stay quiet — Your friends should know who the true King of Silicon Valley is. Once you've bought a sweet helicopter and waterslides for the office, they'll know...It ain't easy staying on top — The market changes. Your marketing team makes (epic) mistakes. Finances are sometimes hard to balance. Your investors don't always think you're the right person for the job. Tread lightly, it looks easier than it is.There's no love in business — You'll be able to steal your friends' employees, trash them in the news and blackmail them into giving you the card you need. Will you be Beta or VHS? — Don't get "Betamaxed". When your business has everything it needs to go public, it's time to IPO. If you can fend off the competition and stay on top, you'll win.What's in the BoxPlease note: The final numbers may shift slightly depending on stretch goals and final rounds of validation.Stretch GoalsThe more money we raise, the better the game becomes. From Serial Entrepreneur Modes to drinking rules and Collusion game cards, there's a lot of goodies we'd like to add to the game. All Amounts USD.What Players Are SayingOver 80 hours of playtest completed with players from around the world. Here’s what players wrote after playing the game:Sacha-Leo Shenkier, Works for a Tech StartupDaniel Tremblay, Developer for a Tech CompanyAndrew Cross, Works for a Tech StartupSimon Vosgueritchian, Works for a Large BusinessGameplayUse of Funds100% of money raised will go towards:
Completing the design work (cards, box and player's guide);
Fulfilling orders;
Making the game better for all players. 
CreditsGame Design: Etienne Garbugli, Aidan Price Graphics & Illustrations: Annejulie Painchaud, Olga UrbanowiczGraphics & Video: François HosyA special thanks to our collaborators and 40+ playtesters for the ideas, support and feedback.Risks and challengesThe game mechanics are fully complete, but we're still working out the exact wording and designs. The main challenges we can see at this point are in balancing the card amounts and gameplay and adjusting the schedule to produce the stretch goals. Thus, we are working to guarantee that the instructions and gameplay are as clear as possible.
